# Histogram Equalization in MATLAB (Using Built-in and Manual Method)

## Purpose
To enhance image contrast using histogram equalization and compare MATLAB’s built-in function with a manually implemented method.

---

## Code Used
```matlab
clc;
clear;
close all;

% Read Original Image
rgb_img = imread('Image.jpeg');

% Convert to Grayscale
gray_img = rgb2gray(rgb_img);
[M, N] = size(gray_img);

% Histogram Equalization Using histeq
histeq_img = histeq(gray_img);

% Manual Histogram Equalization

% Histogram Calculation
hist = zeros(1,256);
for i = 1:M
    for j = 1:N
        intensity = gray_img(i,j);
        hist(intensity + 1) = hist(intensity + 1) + 1;
    end
end

% Probability Density Function
pdf = hist / (M * N);

% Cumulative Distribution Function
cdf = zeros(1,256);
cdf(1) = pdf(1);
for k = 2:256
    cdf(k) = cdf(k-1) + pdf(k);
end

% Transformation Function
T = round(cdf * 255);

% Pixel Mapping
manual_eq_img = zeros(M,N);
for i = 1:M
    for j = 1:N
        manual_eq_img(i,j) = T(gray_img(i,j) + 1);
    end
end
manual_eq_img = uint8(manual_eq_img);

% Display Results
figure('Name','Histogram Equalization Comparison','NumberTitle','off');

subplot(3,3,1); imshow(rgb_img); title('Original RGB');
subplot(3,3,2); imshow(gray_img); title('Grayscale');
subplot(3,3,3); imhist(gray_img); title('Grayscale Histogram');

subplot(3,3,4); imshow(histeq_img); title('histeq Image');
subplot(3,3,5); imhist(histeq_img); title('histeq Histogram');

subplot(3,3,6); imshow(manual_eq_img); title('Manual Equalization');
subplot(3,3,7); imhist(manual_eq_img); title('Manual Histogram');

subplot(3,3,8); axis off;
subplot(3,3,9); axis off;


Operations Performed 

Reads an RGB image

Converts RGB image to grayscale

Enhances contrast using MATLAB histeq

Computes histogram manually

Calculates PDF and CDF

Generates transformation function

Performs manual pixel mapping

Displays original and equalized images with histograms



Output

Original RGB image

Grayscale image and histogram

Histogram equalized image using histeq

Histogram equalized image using manual method

Visual comparison of both techniques



Conclusion

Both built-in and manual histogram equalization improve image contrast. The manual method verifies the working principle behind MATLAB’s histeq function.
